HEADWORD: Cretic
<hw>Cre"tic</hw> <pr>(kr⟦emac⟧"t⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Creticus</ets> (sc. <ets>pes</ets> foot), Gr. <grk>Kritiko`s</grk>
(sc. <grk>poy`s</grk> foot), prop., a Cretan (metrical) foot.]</ety>
<fld>(Gr. & Lat. Pros.)</fld> <def>A poetic foot, composed of one short
syllable between two long ones (- ⟦cre⟧ -).</def>
<rj><au>Bentley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
